article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 88, Green Bay 75
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Anthony Hill scored 29 points and had a double-double to lead Wisconsin-Milwaukee to its fourth straight victory in an 88-75 decision over Wisconsin-Green Bay on Saturday. Hill, who missed tying his career high by one and has reached double figures in eight of his last nine games, went 7 of 8 from the floor and 15 of 18 from the line. He also grabbed a game-high 15 rebounds and blocked three shots. The Panthers (13-11, 8-5 Horizon League) also got 16 points, including four 3-pointers, from Tone Boyle, plus 15 points from Ja'Rob McCallum and 11 points and seven assists from Kaylon Williams. Bryquis Perine led the Phoenix (12-12, 6-6) with 22 points. Rahmon Fletcher scored 16, Jarvis Williams 14 and Daniel Turner 10 for Green Bay, which beat the Panthers 69-64 on Jan. 8. Trailing 5-3, Milwaukee went on a 7-0 run and never trailed again.
